(window["webpackJsonp"]=window["webpackJsonp"]||[]).push([["chunk-d1822694"],{"14eb":function(e,t,i){"use strict";i("184d")},"184d":function(e,t,i){},f770:function(e,t,i){"use strict";i.r(t);var s=i("4430");const n=Object(s["f"])('<section><h1>A design system from Protean Studio</h1><p> This design system is equal parts utility and exploration: we use it both to build web software and to examine what makes a design system valuable. </p><p> The system has an intentionally smaller footprint than others you may have seen. </p><p> A limited scope helped ensure that each part of the system has a clear purpose and immediate value. By sticking only to what we need, we&#39;re able to give ample attention to the foundations of a good design system: </p><ul><li> Accessibility </li><li> Usability and consistent visual language </li><li> Performance and robustness </li><li> A thoughtful API and good developer experience </li></ul></section><section><h2>What is a design system?</h2><p> In brief, we believe a design system is the codification and documentation of a team&#39;s or organization&#39;s design principles. </p><p> For us, that includes web components (<code>protean-elements</code>), styles (<code>protean-styles</code>), the guidelines documented here, and Sketch assets that we use internally. </p><p> Considerations about <em>how</em> and <em>what</em> to codify and document are myriad; ultimately, teams must inform their approach with the particular problems they hope to solve. </p></section><section><h2>Other design systems</h2><p>Below are thoughts on other design systems that we have used and researched. While they share many similarities, their goals and audiences differ.</p><section><h3>Material Design, by Google</h3><p>A popular, extensive design system that Google developed to bring a cohesive design language to their large, diverse product portfolio.</p><p>Material Design&#39;s documentation is remarkably thorough, even offering guidance for applying Machine Learning in design.</p><p><a href="https://material.io/">View Material Design</a></p></section><section><h3>Polaris, by Shopify</h3><p>Shopify&#39;s design system is aimed at developing extensions within the Shopify marketplace ecosystem.</p><p>Like Material Design, Polaris offers a wide palette of components and customizations; where it uniquely shines, however, is the attention given to content guidelines and blueprints for composing entire flows with the components.</p><p><a href="https://polaris.shopify.com/">View Shopify Polaris</a></p></section><section><h3>GOV.UK Design System, US Web Design System</h3><p>Both of these design systems are aimed at improving the public&#39;s experience on government websites.</p><p>Accessibility is imperative in these systems; Javascript use is minimal and every component will work without Javascript.</p><p><a href="https://designsystem.digital.gov/">View the US Web Design System</a></p><p><a href="https://design-system.service.gov.uk/">View the GOV.UK Design System</a></p></section></section>',3);function o(e,t){return n}var a=i("9ad1");class r extends a["b"]{}i("14eb");r.render=o;t["default"]=r}}]);
